                              <item>
                                 <p>Paper, about 12 5/8 in. by 8 5/8, consisting of 199 leaves, some
                                    of which are much stained and slightly torn, especially at the
                                    beginning. The greater part of fol. 28 has been cut away. The
                                    quires are without signatures. The pages are generally divided
                                    into 2 or 3 columns, and the number of lines varies from about
                                    30 to 50.</p>
                              </item>
                           </list>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
